The sample space is the set of all possible outcomes - wikipedia:

&gt; In probability theory, the sample space of an experiment or random trial is the set of all possible outcomes or results of that experiment.

So for example, if the event is the outcome of a die roll then the sample space would be {1,2,3,4,5,6}

